description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/23109/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the European market for tree seedlings. Transport distances are based on eurostat transport statistics

Activity starts with the product leaving the factory gate, ready for shipment.

Activity ends with the reception of the product at the consuming entity. Average transportation requirements from producer to consuming entity are covered.

exchanges.description: Transport based on a wet mas of 0.3 Kg per unit. Transport distance based on eurostat transport statistics for road freight transport. The transport data was extracted from the database leaf 'Annual road freight transport, by type of goods and type of transport [1 000 t, Mio Tkm], from 2008 onwards (road_go_ta_tg)' (http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/data/database) on the 2018-06-01. The transport distance was calculated based on the total mass of goods transported and total payload-distance for the NST 2007 category 'GT01 - Products of agriculture, hunting, and forestry; fish and other fishing products' in the year 2016 for all countries for which data was available. The average distance of road transport for goods in this category in 2016 was 154 km. The fraction of goods transported by road (in terms of mass) relative to the total mass of goods transported by road, rail and inland waterways was 91.7% in 2016. Therefore, the average distance that goods travelled by road in 2016 was 141 km. This value is assumed to be representative for Europe.')

exchanges.description: Transport based on a wet mas of 0.3 Kg per unit. Transport distance based on eurostat transport statistics for railway transport of goods. The transport data was extracted from the database leaf 'Railway transport - goods transported, by group of goods - from 2008 onwards based on NST 2007 (1 000 t, million tkm) (rail_go_grpgood)' (http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/data/database) on the 2018-06-01. The transport distance was calculated based on the total mass of goods transported and total payload-distance for the NST 2007 category 'GT01 - Products of agriculture, hunting, and forestry; fish and other fishing products' in the year 2016 for all countries for which data was available. The average distance of railway transport for goods in this category in 2016 was 265 km. The fraction of goods transported by rail (in terms of mass) relative to the total mass of goods transported by road, rail and inland waterways was 5.5% in 2016. Therefore, the average distance that goods travelled by rail in 2016 was 15 km. This value is assumed to be representative for Europe.
